article.headline: Northeastern 76, Iona 61
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Shawn James recorded the first triple-double in Northeastern history with 17 points, 12 rebounds and a single-game school record 11 blocks to lead the Huskies past Iona 76-61 Thursday night. Jose Juan Barea added 23 points and nine assists for Northeastern (5-5). James, a freshman making his second career start, broke his own school record of seven blocks set against Harvard on Nov. 27. He is now averaging 5.6 blocks per game. Iona (4-7) took its only lead, 14-13, with 11:09 left in the first half. But Northeastern responded with a 26-11 run to pull ahead by 14 at halftime. Iona made a brief surge to pull within 25-21, but James and Barea combined for 10 points during a 14-4 spurt in the final 5:40 of the opening half that gave the Huskies a 39-25 lead. Iona got within 63-56 before James scored on back-to-back possessions to put the game out of reach. Steve Burtt led the Gaels with 19 points. Marcus Barnes added 18 points for Northeastern.
